A-T Families, this is a reminder that by Friday, September 11th, the high school or elementary office needs to be notified if your student intends to choose remote or in person instruction. Next week's schedule( face-to-face instruction in the classroom)

8/31/20
Grades: PK, 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11 (M,W, F)
Grades:K, 2, 4, 6, 8,10,12 (Tues. and Thurs.)

When students are not in the building, they will utilize online instruction as they are currently doing. We realize that the hotspot data usage is a vital concern. That is an issue we are still trying to resolve with the company.

After Labor Day, students have a 4-day week. The schedule will switch.

Tuesday 9//20
Grades: K, 2, 4, 6, 8,10,12 (Tues. &Thurs.)
Grades:: PK, 1, 3, 5,7,9, 11 (Wed. & Fri..)

This schedule is put in place, in the event that we should have a medical situation. Practicing health protocols in and out of the classroom will be a priority. The health situation will be a deciding factor in determining when our students will be in the building at maximum capacity. We will be posting additional updates during the week.

D. Vela, Superintendent
A-T ISD

Immunization Reminder from R3 Health Specialist:

School vaccination rules are in effect for the 2020-2021 school year regardless of whether the education is received via virtual learning or on campus. Information regarding school vaccination rules for the 2020-2021 school year is located on the DSHS Immunization Unit COVID-19 School Updates webpage.

This is posted on R3 website for reference.

School vaccination rules are in effect for the 2020-2021 school year. Students should be up-to-date, in the process of receiving vaccines, or have a valid exemption on file when school starts in the fall. For a list of vaccine requirements for K-12, Pre-K, and child-care facilities, go to the Texas School & Child-Care Facility webpage. For a list of providers who offer low-cost vaccines, go to the Texas Vaccines for Children Provider Locator webpage.

Best,
The School Compliance Team

Amy Carabajal, RN

ECI Program Supervisor

Region 3 ESC School Health Specialist

Reminder:---Class of 2020 Graduation

1) Date – June 12, 2020

2) Time- 7:00pm

3) Site – A-T HS Parking Lot

Families of the graduates will be assigned a designated seating area in the parking lot.

Families will need to bring their own chairs for seating.

Families/guests must stay within their assigned area and practice social distancing from other groups. .

+++We must remember that we cannot congregate in groups before, during, or after the ceremony other than with your own family. This will be strictly enforced.

Additional ceremony attendees without a color coded ticket, will have a designated area for seating apart from the graduates’ families.

Lastly, the school will not be open for any type of public service (restrooms, dressing, drinking water, etc.) This is due to the safety protocol that we must follow upon entry into the buildings. COVID is still very much an issue.

CDC
May 22 at 1:31 PM ·

As summer begins, dive into these tips for enjoying the pool and preventing the spread of the virus that causes COVID-19.

• In or out of the water, stay 6 feet away from people who do not live with you.
• Stay home if you are not feeling well.
• Use cloth face coverings when not in the water. Children under 2 years of age or anyone who has trouble breathing should not use face coverings.
• Limit sharing of pool toys and equipment.

The virus lives in tiny droplets in the lungs of people w/ COVID-19, even when they don’t show symptoms. We can breathe the same air as anyone within abt. 6 ft. of us. Staying farther apart from people during this time reduces the chance of breathing in the virus. #StayHomeTexas

A-T ISD Update:

Due to concerns about the Coronavirus and to support the health and safety of our students, staff, and communities, the Board of Trustees acted on March 16, 2020, to extend school closure through March 29th with students returning back to school on March 30th. Should there be a need to extend the return date even later, the situation will be assessed in a timely manner. We will keep you updated with additional information as soon as it becomes available.

Thank you for your patience and support.
D. Vela
Superintendent
Austwell-Tivoli ISD

Port Aransas Independent School District
February 15 at 12:52 PM ·

PAISD was able to acquire funding to purchase six new buses recently. At the request of our school board, Transportation Director Pete Cowen identified three of our current buses that could be beneficial to another school district. As of Friday, those three buses now belong to Austwell-Tivoli ISD!

North East Independent School District - NEISD helped us out with buses after Hurricane Harvey and now we’re paying it forward!

#strongertogether
#marlinpriderunsdeep
#legacyofexcellence

Today's completion of the playground project was an excellent example to our students that they are supported by the community and their families. For those that worked the past three days preparing food for our workers, thank you! Thank you to Bicki Rudd, Kaboom! and the Rebuild Texas Foundation.

We Appreciate you Austwell-Tivoli!

D. Vela
Supt.
Austwell-Tivoli ISD

Thank you to everyone who came out to help design our future playground. As you could tell, the students were excited and even adults were taking part in activities! This playground is funded by Rebuild Texas and we are proud to be a part of this project. Thank you to the Rebuild Texas Fund and Bicki Rudd with Kaboom Playground. Lastly, thank you to our Redfish Community. We are undertaking a project that will be a positive addition to our children's lives. #WeAreRedfish.
Dolores Vela
A-T ISD

post_text:
Austwell-Tivoli Independent School District will be hosting Usborne Books & More SUMMER BOOK FAIR: JUNE 11TH & 13TH

Courtney Lenhart, our Usborne Books & More Educational Services Representative, will be available at the library during 9AM-11AM and 5PM-7PM to make recommendations for your family.

You can shop for any age (Babies-Young Adult) online, there will be a wide variety of UBAM’s books available at Austwell-Tivoli School on June 11th & 13th (and will include Shine-a-Light “Flashlight” books!). Join us for this fun Summer Book Fair. There will be a sign up for a Summer Book Reading program (where prizes and an end of summer ice cream social will be held.) Best Selling Books will be available to take home from the Book Fair. Exact books from the online site or the catalog can be ordered if not in stock at the book fair.

For more information: https://www.atisd.net/domain/115
Online shop:https://n5154.myubam.com/1299514
